body:
@spulec Looks good!, for me at least.

The original app unit test I had problems with gets the pickling error with 0.1.19 but succeeds with master. The pickling error in the example I reported also goes away with master under Django 1.6 and 1.7.

Thanks for the fix. Could you do a 0.1.20 release to PyPI, assuming no one reports any problems?

I'm more thinking that the code should be:

```
try:
   if attribute_value == real_datetime:
               setattr(module, module_attribute, FakeDatetime)
   if attribute_value == real_date:
                setattr(module, module_attribute, FakeDate)
   if attribute_value == real_time:
                setattr(module, module_attribute, fake_time)
except:
   pass
```

rather than being explicit about which exceptions to catch. But agree that it should be `if/elif` not `if/if`

@bryanhelmig happy to accept a fix.

Agree with thoughts on 1 and 3.

2 makes me a bit nervous. I fear that this would force the majority of users to change their code (that is just a hunch). If we wanted to keep utc default, we could add a `local` argument to override it. As you noted, we will make people upset either way.

@spulec 

>  Are you on master?

